5 and on page 8, lines 43-50, by rewriting the lines to read:
6
7 ""§ 31-71. Definitions.
8 In this Article, the following definitions apply:
9 (1) Electronic. – Relating to technology having electrical, digital, magnetic,
10 wireless, optical, electromagnetic, or similar capabilities.
11 (2) Record. – Information that is inscribed on a tangible medium or that is stored
12 in an electronic or other medium and is retrievable in perceivable form.
13 "§ 31-72. Storage of attested written will by a licensed attorney as an electronic record.
14 (a) At any time during the life of the testator, an attorney licensed to practice law in North
15 Carolina may, at the testator's direction, create an electronic record of the testator's attested
16 written will. The electronic record shall include a certification, signed by that attorney, in the
17 form of an affidavit sworn to or affirmed before an officer authorized to administer oaths, that
18 the electronic record of the attested written will is a complete, true, and accurate copy of the
19 attested written will, that the testator expressly authorized the attorney to create an electronic
20 record of the attested written will, and that the testator has been advised that the creation of an
21 electronic record of the testator's attested written will eliminates the ability of the testator to
22 revoke the attested written will by physical act.";
23
24
25 and on page 9, line 4, by rewriting the line to read:
26
27 ""§ 31-73. Certification of paper copy of attested written will stored as an electronic
28 record.";
29
30
31 and on page 9, line 7, by replacing "G.S. 31-71" with "G.S. 31-72";
