21 "SECTION 8.7. G.S. 31-5.1 reads as rewritten:
22 "§ 31-5.1. Revocation of written will.
23 A written will, or any part thereof, may be revoked only
24 (1) By a subsequent written will or codicil or other revocatory writing executed
25 in the manner provided herein for the execution of written wills, or
26 (2) By being burnt, torn, canceled, obliterated, or destroyed, with the intent and
27 for the purpose of revoking it, by the testator himself or by another person in
28 the testator's presence and by the testator's direction.direction, except as
29 otherwise provided in Article 11 of this Chapter."";
